      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I'm not sure this is a bitcoind bug. It looks like bitcoind would discard a message if ThreadSocketHandler reads a close and sets fDisconnect before ProcessMessages has read the message, but closing right after a send can cause the data to be discarded at the TCP level anyway; why add guarantees at the application level the transport level won't reliably uphold?\n\nSx needs to ensure the tx has been received before closing the connection, by e.g. send tx -> send ping -> wait for pong -> close.\n",
